Hiring a B2B Digital Marketing Agency: 10 Points to Consider

May 29, 2023
|In Digital Marketing
|By Mary-Jane Owen

As a B2B business owner or any business owner, generating sales to keep your business going and make a healthy profit is the goal. In today’s world, utilizing the power of the internet and digital marketing is one of the surefire ways to do that. 

However, hacking the various aspects of digital marketing for effective use is no child’s play. From lead generation, to email marketing, SEO, and demand generation, each element requires specific expertise. This is where B2B digital marketing agencies come in to help.

Choosing the right B2B digital marketing agency can make all the difference between growing your B2B business to a multi-million dollar revenue business and struggling to break even sometimes. 

But with various agency choices to pick from, figuring out which to go with can take time. That’s why we’ve compiled this guide on 10 points to consider while choosing a B2B digital marketing agency. Once you finish reading this guide, you’ll know how to select the appropriate B2B digital marketing agency for your B2B business. 

Why Small and Medium B2B Enterprises Should Consider Partnering with Digital Marketing Agencies

Digital marketing agencies specialize in developing and implementing marketing strategies on different digital platforms such as search engines, social media, and email marketing. 

Partnering with an agency offers access to a team of skilled professionals who can manage all aspects of their digital marketing campaigns. Hence, this helps save valuable resources like time and money. For small and medium enterprises, creating and maintaining an in-house digital marketing team requires significant resources that may not be available to them.

In addition to this, digital marketing agencies possess the knowledge, tools, expertise, and experience required to help businesses stand out in the competitive online marketplace. They understand how to navigate the complexities of the digital landscape and can tailor marketing strategies to each client’s unique needs. 

By creating and executing the right approach, these agencies can help businesses attract more website traffic, generate more leads, and ultimately drive more revenue.

Therefore, partnering with a digital marketing agency can be a wise decision for small and medium B2B enterprises looking to enhance their online presence and achieve their marketing goals.

How Digital Marketing Helps B2B Businesses Differentiate Themselves in a Competitive Landscape

In today’s fiercely competitive marketplace, businesses must discover innovative ways to distinguish themselves from their rivals. With Canada and the US some of the world leaders in various aspects of digital marketing, e.g., spending a combined total of about $175 billion in mobile ad marketing (source: Statista), the North American market is getting hotter by the minute. 

With the emergence of digital technology, an increasing number of B2Bs are adopting digital marketing strategies to differentiate themselves and capture the attention of potential customers.

Digital marketing offers several advantages over traditional marketing methods. For one, it allows businesses to reach a much larger audience through social media, email, and more. Additionally, digital marketing campaigns can be highly targeted, allowing companies to get the right people with the right message at the right time.

In B2B, digital marketing has become essential for businesses seeking a competitive edge. By leveraging digital marketing tactics like SEO, targeted email marketing, paid search advertising, and content marketing, B2B businesses can drive more website traffic, generate more leads, and close more sales.

However, with so many B2B businesses now investing in digital marketing, the competition is fiercer than ever. According to a 2021 survey, 44% of B2B companies believe fiercer competition in the market is making it increasingly harder to generate revenue. To succeed in this space, companies must stay on top of the latest trends and techniques and work with a digital marketing agency that can help them stand out in a crowded marketplace.

By partnering with an agency with the right expertise, experience, and tools, B2B businesses can develop a winning digital marketing strategy that sets them apart from their competitors and drives actual results.

Advantages of Partnering with a B2B Digital Marketing Agency over Building an In-House Marketing Team

While having an in-house marketing team may seem like the ideal solution for B2B businesses, there are several advantages to working with a digital marketing agency instead. Here are a few of the key benefits:

Cost savings

Hiring and training an in-house marketing team can be costly and time-consuming. By working with an agency, businesses can access a team of experienced professionals without worrying about the costs associated with recruitment, training, and ongoing management.

Expertise and knowledge

Digital marketing agencies have teams of professionals who specialize in different areas of digital marketing, such as SEO, PPC, content marketing, and social media marketing. By working with an agency, businesses can access this expertise and knowledge, which can help them develop and implement more effective marketing strategies.

Scalability

When working with an agency, businesses can scale up or down their marketing efforts based on their changing needs allowing for rapid adaptation to changing market conditions and staying ahead of the curve. Having to scale would always be easier when working with agencies as they can always amplify or reduce their efforts, depending on the needs of the company. However, with in-house marketing teams, you need to employ or lay off people, making the whole process more strenuous.

Access to technology and tools

Digital marketing agencies have access to various advanced tools and technologies to help businesses achieve better results from their marketing efforts. Companies can benefit from these tools and technologies by working with an agency without investing in them. Some good examples of these tools include Hootsuite (used to schedule and create content across multiple social media channels), Mailchimp (an email marketing software), and many others used by digital marketers.

Better Analytical Approach

Having an in-house team who understands only your niche is good, however, working with a digital marketing agency is even better. This is because they’ve worked with various businesses in multiple industries, so they have more insights into various strategies used in various industries that could be used in yours too. Also, they can read and analyse data better, provide actionable steps, and implement better changes with these steps.

10 Key Factors to Consider When Choosing A B2B Digital Marketing Agency for SMEs

Choosing the right B2B digital marketing agency to help any small or medium-sized enterprise (SME) grow their business could be quite the Herculean task. With so many agencies to choose from, it can take time to figure out where to start.

To help you make an informed decision, several factors must be considered. From industry expertise and services offered to team members and client retention rates, these factors can help you find an agency to deliver the results you need to grow your business.

Expertise

The agency you choose should have experience and knowledge that aligns with your business needs, such as your industry, target audience, and preferred digital marketing channels. For instance, if you’re in the technology sector, you need an agency that understands the challenges and trends in that space. Similarly, if you’re targeting financial professionals, you need an agency to create tailored campaigns for that audience. 

You could also access the expertise of the preferred agency by asking them to provide case studies, and look up reviews of their agency on independent platforms. You could also talk to other companies they’ve worked with before for testimonies.

Customization

Your business has unique needs, and a one-size-fits-all marketing approach won’t be practical. An agency offering a customized approach will tailor their strategies to fit your business goals, target audience, and industry. You get the best value for your money by avoiding unnecessary services or tactics that may not be relevant to your business. With a tailored approach, you can reach your target audience more effectively, generate more leads, and ultimately grow your business. You could also access an agency on this by checking out their various approaches to previous clients. Do they use specified approaches for each of their clients? Or do they have a rigid approach in most of their case studies? This helps you to judge how well they can pivot if a strategy doesn’t work.

Reputation

A good reputation indicates a track record of success and reliability. To evaluate an agency’s reputation, research its website carefully. Check their ‘about us’ page to understand what their mission and values are, their approach to helping clients, and so on. Also, read case studies and client testimonials, and check online review sites. A strong reputation also means the agency has a network within your industry, providing opportunities for partnerships and collaborations. 

Data-driven

The agency you choose should focus on data and metrics to ensure they make data-driven decisions based on real-world results. This means that they should be using analytics tools and platforms to track the performance of their campaigns and make data-driven decisions about optimizing and improving them. It’s essential to look for a team with experience working with data and analytics which can show you how they have used data to optimize campaigns for previous clients. The agency should be able to explain its approach to data-driven marketing clearly and should be able to demonstrate how they have used data to improve campaign performance in the past.

Innovation

An innovative agency will bring fresh ideas and approaches, helping your business stand out in a competitive marketplace. Look for an agency constantly adapting and evolving to stay ahead of industry trends and changes. Innovation and technology can ensure that your marketing strategies are practical and thriving in the long run.

Long-term Partnership

When choosing a B2B digital marketing agency, thinking about the long-term is essential. You want to avoid being in a position where you must switch agencies frequently, as this can disrupt your marketing efforts and harm your brand’s reputation. A good agency will work to build a long-term partnership with your business to help you achieve sustained growth over time. To establish a long-term partnership, the agency should take the time to understand your business, its goals, and its challenges. They should be willing to work with you to develop strategies and campaigns aligned with your long-term goals rather than just providing quick fixes that may deliver short-term results.

Communication

The agency you choose should be able to communicate clearly and effectively with you throughout the entire process, from understanding your business needs to executing marketing campaigns. They should be responsive, available to answer your questions and provide regular updates on progress and results. Communication can lead to better understanding, delays, and effective marketing strategies. Be sure to choose an agency that values clear and timely communication to ensure the success of your marketing efforts.

Research

It’s essential to consider their research capabilities. A good agency should have a robust research process to understand your business, target audience, and industry. This will help them develop effective strategies and campaigns that deliver results. Look for an agency that uses data-driven insights to inform their marketing decisions, as this will help you achieve a better return on investment.

Pricing Structure

You’d definitely have a budget you’re working with when hiring a digital marketing agency. This major factor will come into play when picking the final choice. You need to know if they charge a flat fee or a percentage of ad spend. Ensure you understand their pricing structure and if it fits your budget.

The Onboarding Process

Before making the final step into the water, ensure you fix a meeting with your prospects to see how easy it will be to onboard into your company’s process. You need to ensure they understand your business and what it needs. Do they understand your ideal customer profiles (ICPs), personas, and target audience? You need to ensure you can get the train running off as soon as possible.
